  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="dc1d-558b-8bdf-d49e" name="Hate High Elves" hidden="false">
      <description>Reroll missed hits on first round of combat.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="102b-545f-1fcd-2452" name="Thick Skinned" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="8" hidden="false">
      <description>A cold one has scaly skin which acts like armour giving the rider a +2 Armour save for being mounted insread of normal +1</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3cfb-55da-b19b-9dfb" name="Impale" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="14" hidden="false">
      <description>A dark Pegasus uses its horn when charging giving a +1S on charge.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f620-0e40-238c-3c85" name="Noxious Breath" hidden="false">
      <description>Breath Weapon, any units taking casualties from this ttack must pass a leadership next turn in order to charge. Does not effect undead or daemons although damage as normal.
</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="1199-8fdc-3d41-eedd" name="Sect Enmity" hidden="false">
      <description>May not join a unit with an Assassin</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f017-feeb-a6c1-85e2" name="Beastmaster" hidden="false">
      <description>Any monster within 12" taking a monster reaction test may reroll ld
Monster mounts of beastmaster will fight as normal, no reaction test.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="5502-b542-26bc-ce94" name="Devotee of Khaine" hidden="false">
      <description>Cannot be joined by characters, except Assassin</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="97de-5f48-d5a8-9366" name="Beasts" hidden="false" />
    <rule id="a72d-333d-2ed1-05e5" name="Repeater Bolt Thrower" hidden="false" />
    <rule id="02cc-9713-1c7e-144a" name="Hatred" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="6" hidden="false">
      <description>Hatred: Black Guard arc vicious killers and bate everybody and everything (see page 84-85 of the Warhammer rulebook for the rules for hatred). </description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="65eb-ff09-1a54-d068" name="Stubborn" hidden="false">
      <description>Raised from birth to protect the Witch King himself, Black Guard would rather die than give ground. Black Guard are stubborn (see page 85 of the Warhammer rulebook). 
</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8f91-2aba-9489-fbc1" name="Dance of Doom" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="23" hidden="false">
      <description>The model has a 5+ ward save</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="5e13-4ed2-9dc1-0e3b" name="Executioner's Axe" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="18" hidden="false">
      <description>When rolling to wound and for armour saves, the bearer counts as having a Strength double that of the targets toughness. Two Handed Weapon. Always Strikes Last except in the turn it charges.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9d5f-0395-ff6c-d901" name="Venom Sword" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="18" hidden="false">
      <description>Any model which suffers a wound to the Venom sword must roll equal to or under their toughtness on 2d6 or be slain.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="40f2-8761-75f9-8931" name="Blade of Ruin" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="18" hidden="false">
      <description>No armour save may be taken for wounds from this blade. Ward saves are taken as normal.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="eb55-003d-29d7-375b" name="Hydra Blade" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="18" hidden="false">
      <description>Gain D3 attacks each Close combat phase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b3e7-0c89-8e3b-ea9f" name="Crimson Death" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="18" hidden="false">
      <description>Always Strikes with Strength of 6. No other modifiers will effect this. Requires Two Hands</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="4808-7fe7-0cd4-7ba3" name="Lifetaker" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="18" hidden="false">
      <description>Lifetaker is treated as a repeating crossbow but always hits on 2+ regardless of modifiers. You may reroll failed to wound rolls.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="751d-c666-007b-70bf" name="Web of Shadows" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="18" hidden="false">
      <description>One Use Only.
A web of shadows can only be used once per game. The character uses the Web of Shadows instead of normal attacks. When used , one model in b2b contact automatically take 2D6 str3 hits. The bearer may take a non magical weapon but not another magical weapon.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9f92-c204-eff6-c13a" name="Heartseeker" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="19" hidden="false">
      <description>You may reroll missed attacks. Remember a dice can never be rerolled more than once.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e245-de57-8b31-a4a5" name="Chill Blade" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="19" hidden="false">
      <description>Any model wounded by this blade after saves ect may not attack this round.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="c05a-cfd3-5794-34a4" name="Dark Sword" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="19" hidden="false">
      <description>Models wounded by this blade subject to stupidity for rest of the battle</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="dbe4-ce91-fb65-e019" name="Ring of Darkness" publicationId="d82e-5e6d-5df0-8ddd" page="20" hidden="false">
      <description>Bound Spell: Power level 3
Attacks in CC require a 6 to hit the bearer regardless of WS or modifiers. Remains in Play</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3c24-140a-609e-eec0" name="Armour of Living Death" hidden="false">
      <description>Counts as heavy armour (+5 sv) which can be combined with other armor as normal.  In addition the model gains +1T and +1 W.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e855-040a-b9ca-ef84" name="Armour of Eternal servitude" hidden="false">
      <description>This couints as light armour (+6 save) and may be combined with other armour as normal. In addition the character gains 'Regeneration'</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6c1f-c718-bccb-033d" name="Shield of Ghrond" hidden="false">
      <description>Treated like a normal shield but attackers strength is reduced by 1</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6273-5c62-6732-fa04" name="Armour of Darkness" hidden="false">
      <description>The armour includes a shield and gives a 2+ armour save which cannot be improved in anyway.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="34bf-96d2-f26d-2153" name="Blood Armour" hidden="false">
      <description>Blood armour is heavy armour +5 sve and can be combined with other armour as normal. For every wound the bearer inflicts after saves, the armour save is increased by 1 to a maximum of +1</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="041b-79ac-a50f-5d86" name="Seal of Ghrond" hidden="false">
      <description>Adds 1 Dice to the Dispel pool</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b926-4eec-8b36-0e9f" name="Darkstar Cloak" hidden="false">
      <description>Gives +1 Power dice, only usuable by that sorcerer.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ff82-a689-234a-039a" name="Draich of Dark Power" hidden="false">
      <description>+2 Str, Killing Blow, Uses two hands</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3065-ea54-0e95-cd56" name="Blade of Spite" hidden="false">
      <description>Any hit rolls of 5 or 6 automatically wound, with no need to roll to wound.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="17d1-3798-1d4b-e445" name="Heart-Stone of Darkness" hidden="false">
      <description>The bearer has a 4+ ward save</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6d3f-7b16-cd1f-7b0d" name="Wand of Kharaidon" hidden="false">
      <description>Bound Spell Power Level 4
Once per magic phase, the bearer may cast the spell Doombolt. Each time the wand is used roll a d6, on a 1 the wand is exhaunsted and can no longer be used.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="5705-63b1-3a31-ea2a" name="The Cloak of  Dark Souls" hidden="false">
      <description>Character may "Scout" if on foot.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="945c-e347-8fd0-3f96" name="Soul Shadows Standard" hidden="false">
      <description>The unit may make a flee response (Even if immune to pyschology) and will always wutomatical rally at the end of its flee movement providing it is not causght by pursuers.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="sost-danc-dead-0001" name="Dance of Death" hidden="false">
      <description>The Sisters of Slaughter may negate an enemy's rank bonus when determining combat resolution, even though they are Skirmishers. However, they must still meet the normal requirements (Unit Strength 5 or more and charging the enemy in the flank or rear). Remember that this effect also negates the Skaven rank bonus to Leadership.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="doom-ward-save-0001" name="Ward Save (6+)" hidden="false">
      <description>The Doomfire Warlocks have a Ward save of 6+.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="doom-magi-unit-0001" name="Magical Unit (&quot;Doombolt of Kharaidon&quot;)" hidden="false">
      <description>In the Magic phase, the unit, provided it is not fleeing, may cast the spell "Doombolt of Kharaidon" as if it were a bound spell with a Power Level equal to the unit's current number of models at the moment of casting. The unit counts as a wizard for this purpose, but does not generate any power or dispel dice and cannot attempt to dispel spells. The unit itself casts the spell and it cannot be negated by items or effects that nullify magical items. All restrictions of the spell must always be observed (line of sight, casting into close combat, and so on).</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="medu-petr-gaze-0001" name="Petrifying Gaze" hidden="false">
      <description>The Medusa's Petrifying Gaze is treated as a ranged attack. Any model hit by this attack must pass a Toughness test or be turned to stone and removed as a casualty, regardless of Wounds. This attack ignores armour saves. Ward saves may still be taken. The Medusa may not use the Petrifying Gaze in the same turn she shoots with a bow.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="medu-soli-tary-0001" name="Solitary" hidden="false">
      <description>Medusae are treated as Monsters.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="khar-aqua-tic0-0001" name="Aquatic" hidden="false">
      <description>The Kharibdys may move through water terrain without penalty and is never slowed by it.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="khar-hand-ler0-0001" name="Handler" hidden="false">
      <description>The Kharibdys is accompanied by 2 Handlers. As long as at least one Handler is alive, the Kharibdys is Immune to Psychology. If all Handlers are slain, the Kharibdys must test for Stupidity each turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="khar-rave-maw0-0001" name="Ravenous Maw" hidden="false">
      <description>One of the Kharibdys' attacks must be made using a differently coloured die. This attack inflicts D6 Wounds.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="khar-abys-howl-0001" name="Abyssal Howl" hidden="false">
      <description>Enemy units that are in base contact with one or more Kharibdyss suffer -1 Leadership (to a minimum of 2).</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="blck-amul-rule-0001" name="Black Amulet" hidden="false">
      <description>The wearer has a 5+ Ward save against close combat hits. If the wearer passes his Ward save then the attacking model suffers 1 wound instead. There is no save against such a rebounded wound, even from Wards.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="crwn-iron-rule-0001" name="Crown of Black Iron" hidden="false">
      <description>The character has a 5+ Ward save. In addition, the wearer is completely immune to the effects of Light Magic and High Magic spells. Note that this is not a Dispel and thus other models (excluding the character's mount) may be affected by High Magic and Light Magic.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ring-hotek-rule-0001" name="Ring of Hotek" hidden="false">
      <description>Any magic user (friend or foe) attempting to cast a spell within 6" of the wearer will miscast on the roll of any double. If they roll a double 6 they cast the spell (with Irresistible Force) and then suffer a Miscast.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="dead-mask-terr-0001" name="Deathmask" hidden="false">
      <description>The wearer causes Terror.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
